<h2>Linux</h2>
Linux operating systems usually have Python and Sphinx pre-installed. To check and install Sphinx (if needed),
<ol>
<li> Install the Git tool. Find instructions <a href="https://git-scm.com/">here</a>. </li> <br />
<li> Install GNU Make. Find instructions <a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/make/">here</a>. </li><br />
Follow the steps for your Linux O.S:
<p><br /><br />
<b> Ubuntu </b>
<br />Run:<br />

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-scss" data-lang="scss"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="nt">apt-get</span> <span class="nt">install</span> <span class="nt">python3-sphinx</span>
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<br />
<b> Fedora </b>
<br />Run:<br />

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-scss" data-lang="scss"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="nt">sudo</span> <span class="nt">dnf</span> <span class="nt">install</span> <span class="nt">python3-sphinx</span>
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></figure>

<br />
<b> Archlinux </b>
<br />
You can find the official package for Sphinx <a href="https://www.archlinux.org/packages/community/any/python-sphinx/"> here.</a> <br />Download and install or run the following command.
<br />Run:<br />

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-scss" data-lang="scss"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
</pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="nt">pacman</span> <span class="nt">-S</span> <span class="nt">python-sphinx</span> <span class="nt">3</span><span class="nc">.1.1-1</span>
